# Driver Drowsiness Detection System

## Overview

The Driver Drowsiness Detection System is an AI-based application that detects a driver's state in real time using a webcam. The system classifies the driver into one of three categories—Focused, Drowsy, or Distracted—and helps improve road safety by identifying signs of fatigue or distraction.

The project uses a Teachable Machine image classification model integrated with Python, TensorFlow/Keras, and OpenCV for real-time predictions.

---

## Features

- Real-time webcam-based driver monitoring
- Detects three driver states:
  - Focused
  - Drowsy
  - Distracted
- Displays prediction confidence
- Live video feed with prediction labels
- User-friendly interface
- Easy integration with custom trained models

---

## Technologies Used

- Python
- TensorFlow / Keras
- OpenCV
- NumPy
- Teachable Machine
- Google Colab

